{"lemma":"باطِنُو","slug":"باطِنُو","root":"ب.ط.ن","root_slug":"ب-ط-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ط-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"باطِن","root":"بطن","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2816"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B7%D9%90%D9%86%D9%8F%D9%88"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"interior, inner"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"intrinsic"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"secret"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of بَطَنَ (baṭana, “to be hidden, to hide”), from the root ب ط ن (b ṭ n); compare بَطْن (baṭn, “stomach, womb, interior”)."},"ipa":["/baː.tˤin/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2816","headword_ar":"بَاطِنٌ","root":"bTn","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Unapparent; hidden; concealed; covert:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) [and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inward; inner; interior; internal; intrinsic; esoteric:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in all these senses]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZaAhirN","text_ar":"ظَاهِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baATinu A^amorK","text_ar":"بَاطِنُ اَمْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The inward,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intrinsic, state"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"circumstances, of a case"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an affair"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (TA, &c.;) [and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amorK","text_ar":"اَمْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baTonu","text_ar":"بَطْنُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; whence the phrases,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afora$aniY Zahora A^amorihi wabaTonahu","text_ar":"اَفْرَشَنِى ظَهْرَ اَمْرِهِ وَبَطْنَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He displayed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"laid open, to me the outward state"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"circumstances of his case"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair, and the inward state"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"circumstances thereof"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa","text_ar":"هُوَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mujar~ibN baTona AlA^umuwri","text_ar":"مُجَرِّبٌ بَطْنَ الاُمُورِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is one who possesses experience of the inward,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intrinsic, state"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"circumstances of affairs"},{"kind":"text","text":"], as though he hit their bellies by his knowledge of their true, or real, states or circumstances. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaATinu","text_ar":"البَاطِنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The internal, inward,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intrinsic, state, condition, character,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"circumstances,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a man: and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the heart,"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the secret thoughts; the recesses of the mind; the state of mind; the inward,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"secret, disposition of the mind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlZ~aAhiru","text_ar":"الظَّاهِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b4-  Also,] an epithet applied to God, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He who knows the inward,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intrinsic, states"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"circumstances of things:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or He who knows the secret and hidden things:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He who is veiled from the eyes and imaginations of created beings."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baATinFA","text_ar":"بَاطِنًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Covertly; secretly."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b6-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baATinapN","text_ar":"بَاطِنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in eight places. ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biTaAnapN","text_ar":"بِطَانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A water-course,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place in which water flows, in rugged ground:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buTonaAnN","text_ar":"بُطْنَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buTonN","text_ar":"بُطْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","S"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}